<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-08-08T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-08-08T14:00:00-05:00" n="442" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d442">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">711.94/1608: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Grew</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-08-08T15:00:00-04:00">August 8, 1940—3
                                        p.m.</date></dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>296. Your 619, July 26, 5 p.m.,<note n="39" xml:id="d442fn39">Not
                                    printed, but see memorandum by the Ambassador in Japan, July 26,
                                        <ref target="frus1931-41v02#pg_104"><hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, Japan, 1931–1941, vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">ii</hi>, p. 104</ref>.</note> paragraph
                                3. The Foreign Minister’s message to the Secretary was delivered to
                                the Secretary upon his return from Habana and before his subsequent
                                departure from Washington on brief leave. As opportunity offers
                                please convey to the Foreign Minister an expression of the
                                Secretary’s appreciation and of his assurance that he shares the
                                Foreign Minister’s views with regard to the importance of
                                Japanese-American relations.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Welles</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>